'''Fedor Georgievich Alekseev''' ({{lang-rus|Федор Алексеев}}, {{lang-hy|Ֆեոդոր Ալեքսեև}}) is a [[Russia]]n and [[Armenia]]n [[linguist]] and [[journalist]] of [[Belarusians|Belarusian]] origin.
He is the editor-in-chief of ''Minority Languages'', a Russian academic journal dedicated to [[endangered languages|endangered]] [[languages of Russia]],<ref>[https://elibrary.ru/title_about.asp?id=63754 "Minority Languages". Russian Science Citation Index] (in Russian).</ref> and ''Kamysh'', a local online magazine based in the city of [[Astrakhan]] in Southern Russia.<ref>[https://kamysh.press/alekseev Fedor Alekseev. Kamysh] (in Russian).</ref>
