The 2009 [[World Solar Challenge]] was one of a biennial series of [[Solar car racing|solar-powered car races]], covering {{convert|3021|km|mi|abbr=on}} through the Australian [[Outback]], from [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]], [[Northern Territory]] to [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]].
In the Challenge class 24 teams started, of which eight completed the course, and the winner was [[Tokai University]] of Japan. In the Adventure class seven teams started and two completed the course, the winner being [[Osaka Sangyo University]] also of Japan.
